{
  "texts": [
    "Ethical safeguards have been put in place to preserve the confidentiality of data and to secure the informed consent of interviewees.",
    "However, the asymmetrical relationship between the researcher asking for information and the respondent giving up potentially sensitive information about themselves remains.",
    "Informed consent has been the cornerstone of the privacy paradigm.",
    "We explore in the following section how privacy harms are exacerbated by the mass-scale extraction and storage of personal and sensitive data, as well as, potentially, the public release of granular predictions.",
    "Consider these two examples from real-world applications, already highlighted above."
  ]
}